EXPLANATION – Matter in bolded italics is new; matter between brackets [omitted material] is material to be omitted.
AN ACT relating to state financial administration; requiring the
transfer of certain money from the Account to Stabilize
the Operation of the State Government to the State
General Fund; and providing other matters properly
relating thereto.
Legislative Counsel’s Digest:
1 The Account to Stabilize the Operation of the State Government, also known as
2 the Rainy Day Account, is an account into which surplus state revenues are
3 deposited to be used in case of fiscal emergencies. (NRS 353.288) This bill
4 transfers money from the Account to the State General Fund in Fiscal Years 2025-
5 2026 and 2026-2027.
THE PEOPLE OF THE STATE OF NEVADA, REPRESENTED IN
SENATE AND ASSEMBLY, DO ENACT AS FOLLOWS:
1 Section 1. The State Controller shall transfer from the
2 Account to Stabilize the Operation of the State Government created
3 by NRS 353.288 to the State General Fund the sum of $288,742,305
4 in Fiscal Year 2025-2026 and $61,813,016 in Fiscal Year 2026-
5 2027 for unrestricted State General Fund use.
6 Sec. 2. This act becomes effective on July 1, 2025.
